The system needs to have the ability to run database migration during the deployment process instead of running the script manually and separately as now to ensure the missing of database upgrading and reduce the deployment downtime.  Please implement this and also have a guideline for all developers to follow when they want to make a database change.

*Apply Database Migration With* {color:#ff5630}*Flyway*{color} *library.*

# Add Flyway library into {color:#ff5630}build.gradle {color}of service which apply DB migration. 
{noformat}implementation("org.flywaydb:flyway-core"){noformat}
# Change hibernate config (application.yml) to {color:#ff5630}validate{color} (we will create new table by migration not hibernate).
{noformat}hibernate:
  hbm2ddl:
    auto: validate{noformat}
# Config Flyway on application.properties
{noformat}#Database Migration - Flyway
spring.flyway.baseline-on-migrate=true{noformat}
# Create new {color:#ff5630}/db/migration{color} folder under {color:#ff5630}/src/main/resources/{color} folder.
# Create migration sql file in folder {color:#ff5630}/src/main/resources/db/migration{color}. Example: {color:#00b8d9}V1.0.1__create_history_table.sql{color}
{code:sql}CREATE TABLE car (
    id INT NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY,
    license_plate VARCHAR NOT NULL,
    color VARCHAR NOT NULL
);

ALTER TABLE owner ADD driver_license_id VARCHAR;

INSERT INTO brand (name) VALUES ('DeLorean');{code}
# Start up service, Flyway will execute all sql script in {color:#ff5630}src/main/resources/db/migration{color} folder.



*Flyway Notes*

# Naming must comply with the following naming pattern
!image-20210527-022316.png|width=872,height=462!
# To disable auto migration by Flyway. Set config on application_env.properties of environment which don’t want execute migration.
{noformat}spring.flyway.enabled=false{noformat}
# Flyway add new record into {color:#ff5630}flyway_schema_history{color} table to track project’s migration.
!image-20210527-032409.png|width=1504,height=128!
# *Impotant note:* Sql script only execute by migration when it’s version is greater than version which store in {color:#ff5630}flyway_schema_history{color} table.
# About rule’s Flyway, please reference to: [https://flywaydb.org/documentation/concepts/migrations#overview|https://flywaydb.org/documentation/concepts/migrations#overview|smart-link] 



*Auto execute SQL script on Production Env*

